<edge source="Noah Carter" target="World Athletics Federation">
  <data key="d7">28.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The World Athletics Federation is responsible for overseeing both the rules and regulations as well as the validation of records for athletes such as Noah Carter. This federation ensures that Noah Carter adheres to specific guidelines during his participation in international competitions, including championship events, thereby maintaining the integrity and standards of athletic performance. The World Athletics Federation validates new records set by Noah Carter at these major events, ensuring they meet all required criteria under their established regulations. It oversees the validation and recognition of records set by athletes such as Noah Carter, confirming that these records are compliant with the rules and validations specified for athletes participating in championships. This includes validating Noah Carter's recent 100m sprint record to ensure it adheres to all necessary criteria under their regulations. The World Athletics Federation plays a crucial role in overseeing the rules and ensuring compliance for athletes like Noah Carter, facilitating fair competition and maintaining high standards across international athletic events.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees the competition where Noah Carter broke a record and ensures compliance with rules regarding equipment use.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees record validations for athletes like Noah Carter.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees the validation of Noah Carter's new 100m sprint record.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees the rules and validations for records set at competitions like the one where Noah Carter broke the 100m sprint record.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees the validation of records set by athletes like Noah Carter.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees Noah Carter's achievement in the 100m sprint record at the championship.</data>
